Today commemorates the 50th anniversary of the signing of the Voting Rights Act by President Lyndon Baines Johnson. Without the VRA, many of the gains established in the Civil Rights Act of 1964 would have gone unfulfilled. The right to vote enshrined in the VRA made the legal portion of our nation's great civil rights revolution a living reality.

No more could literacy tests and other mechanisms of voter repression be used to deny African-Americans their civil rights under the law.
